article.headline: Louisiana-Lafayette routs South Alabama 102-76

inlines.body:
More Bulls-Knicks Coverage

In the prolonged absence of Derrick Rose, and after a record-setting performance for a center, Joakim Noah has become the face and personality of the team, Michael Wilbon writes. Story

Having won nine of 10 games, the Bulls believe in themselves again and that, even without Derrick Rose and the traded Luol Deng, they will beat any team they match up against, Nick Friedell writes. Blog

After the Knicks fell behind by 25 in the first half against the Bulls on Sunday, Carmelo Anthony called his team out and complimented the Bulls, which reminded of his impending free agency, Ian Begley writes. Blog

• Rapid Reaction: Bulls | Knicks
• ESPN Chicago | ESPN New York

article.story:
LAFAYETTE, La. -- Bryant Mbamalu scored a career-high 32 points and grabbed 11 rebounds as Louisiana-Lafayette routed South Alabama 102-76 on Sunday.

Mbamalu made 10 of 19 from the field, hitting 5 of 7 from 3-point range as Louisiana-Lafayette (19-10, 10-6 Sun Belt Conference) shot 61.7 percent from the field and 8 of 12 from beyond the arc.

Shawn Long added 20 points and 10 rebounds and J.J. Davenport scored 11 points for the Ragin' Cajuns, who led 52-27 at halftime. Louisiana-Lafayette held a 47-27 advantage in rebounding.

It marks the fourth time this season that the Ragin' Cajuns have scored more than 100 points and the second against a Division I opponent. Louisiana-Lafayette has now won seven of its last eight.

Ken Williams led South Alabama with 24 points and Augustine Rubit added 17, but the Jaguars (9-20, 3-13) shot just 37.9 percent from the field.
